<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Solving over-contrained block-level replaced elements in normal flow</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="HTMLonly" />
        <meta name="assert" content="When direction is 'ltr', margin-right is ignored in an over-constrained situation." />
        <style type="text/css">
            .c1
            {
                background-color: green;
                border: solid 1px black;
                width: 25px;
                height: 25px;
                float: left;
            }
            div
            {
                width: 200px;
                height: 50px;
            }
            p
            {
                width: 50%;
            }
            textarea
            {
                margin-left: auto;
                margin-right: 10px;
                width: 25px;
                height: 25px;
                border: solid 1px black;
                float: left;
                background-color: blue;
                overflow: hidden;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div>
            <span class="c1"></span>
            <textarea cols="1" rows="1"></textarea>
            <span class="c1"></span>
        </div>
        <p>No space should be between the green box on the left and the blue box. A space should be between the blue box and the right green box.</p>
    </body>
</html>